31/07/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- By a wide margin Thursday (July 30th), parliament supported a 1% VAT hike proposed by the cabinet. 
The higher rate, 23%, takes effect on Saturday and is one of the key measures aimed at boosting revenues. 
Parliament also approved the introduction of a 6% tax on mobile telephony revenues, effective Saturday, as well as changes to the tax rates on luxury cars and yachts. 
(HINA, HRT - 30/07/09)
